      "value": "<p><em>Biome: Underdark & Caves</em></p>\\n<p>Bulbous, ivory-colored fungus that releases a 10-foot cloud of spores when disturbed. The spores act as an inhaled poison (DC Constitution 15, [[/roll 1d8-1]] poison damage). If a target takes damage from the spores, their bone density is reduced, increasing vulnerability to bludgeoningâ€”rolls of 19 or 20 count as critical hits against the affected creature. The fungi are immune to acid and thunder; they are destroyed by cold or radiant damage. Fire and electricity also destroy them but release spores. Recovery from reduced bone density requires magical remedies such as potion effects or the Lesser Restoration spell.</p>",
